CHEFLAND LIBRARAY
In Chefland Library, there is a penalty system for returning books late.

Rules for penalties:

If a book is returned late by d days, the penalty for that book is d points.

If multiple books are returned on the same day, only the largest penalty among those books is counted for that day.

Chef borrowed N books. For the i-th book:

It was returned i days late.

It was returned on day Aᵢ.

Your task is to calculate the total penalty points Chef must pay.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer T — the number of test cases.

For each test case:

The first line contains an integer N — the number of books.

The second line contains N space-separated integers A₁, A₂, …, Aₙ, where Aᵢ represents the day the i-th book was returned.

Output Format

For each test case, print one integer — the total penalty points Chef must pay.

Explanation of Sample Test Case 3

Input:

N = 4
A = [1, 1, 2, 1]

Books:

Book 1 → returned on day 1, late by 1 day

Book 2 → returned on day 1, late by 2 days

Book 3 → returned on day 2, late by 3 days

Book 4 → returned on day 1, late by 4 days

Grouping by return day:

Day 1: books with penalties 1, 2, 4 → take the maximum = 4

Day 2: book with penalty 3

Total penalty = 4 + 3 = 7

SOLUTION::::


import java.util.*;
import java.lang.*;
import java.io.*;

class Codechef
{
	public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception
	{
		Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
		int t=s.nextInt();
		while(t-->0){
		    int n=s.nextInt();
		    int a[]=new int[n];
		    int m=-1;
		    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		        a[i]=s.nextInt();
		        m=Math.max(m,a[i]);
		    }
		    int b[]=new int[m+1];
		    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		        b[a[i]]=i+1;
		    }
		    int k=0;
		    for(int i=0;i<=m;i++){
		        k+=b[i];
		    }
		    System.out.println(k);
		}

	}
}
